## Key Context for Families

**Critical Update**: Indiana's senior property tax program underwent major changes in 2026. If your elderly loved one was receiving benefits before 2026, their benefit structure may have changed[6][7].

**Two Programs Available**:
- **Over 65 Credit**: A flat $150 credit on the property tax bill (new as of 2026)[6]
- **Over 65 Circuit Breaker Credit**: Caps property tax increases at 2% year-over-year[1]

Seniors may qualify for one or both programs[7].

**Income Limits Are the Primary Gatekeeper**: For 2026 taxes, AGI cannot exceed $60,000 (single) or $70,000 (married)[1]. These limits increase annually with Social Security adjustments[1].

**Homestead Deduction Is Required**: To qualify for the Over 65 Credit, your loved one must have received (or currently qualify for) the homestead deduction on the same property[6]. This is a prerequisite many families miss.

**Application Deadline**: January 15 of the year taxes are due[1][7]. Contact your county auditor's office to apply; there is no statewide online portal—each county handles applications separately[7].
